                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d693">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.00111 Armament Control/215: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-18T11:00:00+02:35"
                            >October 18, 1935—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 12:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>135. Minister of Foreign Affairs as president of the Ethiopian Red Cross requests
                    that permission be granted for the exportation of several American ambulance
                    planes intended for Ethiopia. He states that the American authorities have
                    refused such permission but he hopes that in view of lack of roads in that
                    country decision will be reconsidered. Early reply will be appreciated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
